'''Mark Mom''' is a [[Papua New Guinea]]n [[rugby league]] player who represented [[Papua New Guinea national rugby league team|his country]] in the [[2000 Rugby League World Cup|2000 World Cup]].
==Playing career==
Mom attended [[St John's College, Woodlawn]] in [[Australia]] and played for the [[Australian Schoolboys rugby league team|Australian Schoolboys']] side. 

In 1994 he played for the [[Papua New Guinea national rugby league team|Papua New Guinea]] side at the 1994 [[Rugby League World Sevens|World Sevens]].<ref>[http://www.postcourier.com.pg/20110207/sport01.htm Former Kumul gunned down] ''postcourier.com.pg'', 7 February 2011</ref>

Between 1996 and 2001 he played eight test matches for the Kumuls, including four at the [[2000 Rugby League World Cup|2000 World Cup]].<ref name=rlp/>
